## _Game made by Minder Singh, Matt Jadro & Josiah Buxton_

## **Abstract**

**Hot Takes** is an anonymous social media and mobile game (iOS \+ Android) where players share their most unfiltered opinions‚Äîcalled _Hot Takes_‚Äîfor others to rate on a Scoville Unit scale of **0 to 100**. The app merges the virality of social platforms like Twitter with the gamified engagement of casual mobile games.

Players submit short, opinionated statements about life, culture, sports, or anything they desire. Others rate these Takes, with all ratings averaged into a ‚ÄúHeat Score.‚Äù The highest-scoring Hot Take each week wins a **monetary jackpot**, starting at **$20** and scaling up to **$100** based on total active players that week.

The core gameplay loop‚Äîsubmit ‚Üí rate ‚Üí see results ‚Üí chase leaderboard‚Äîdrives retention and competitive participation. The business objective is **user growth and engagement** to **maximize ad revenue** via strategically placed in-feed ad slots. The more users participate, the more valuable the ad inventory becomes, directly linking engagement growth to revenue scalability.

## **Game Rules**

1. **Free to Play:** Players can submit as many Hot Takes as they want each week.

2. **Eligibility:** Players must create an account and link a **Venmo**, **Square**, or **PayPal** handle to receive payouts.

3. **Voting:** Each Take can be rated on a **0‚Äì100 Scoville Unit scale** using a slider and ‚ÄúSubmit‚Äù button. The player‚Äôs score is averaged into the Take‚Äôs ongoing average and then displayed alongside the community average.

4. **Winning:** The player whose Hot Take achieves the highest **average score** by week‚Äôs end wins the monetary jackpot.

5. **Prize Scaling:**

   - Base pot: **$20**

   - Increases to **$100** as more players submit Takes (see Rewards section for scaling details).

6. **Hall of Flame:** Displays the **top 3 Takes** of the prior week, ranked by Heat Score.

7. **Wall of Flame (Homepage):** Displays a live feed of all current week‚Äôs Hot Takes to be rated.

8. **Community Fairness:** Feed prioritizes under-rated Takes to ensure visibility for all players.

9. **Account Requirements:** All players must agree to **Terms of Service** and **Privacy Policy** to participate.

## **Screens**

### **Screen 0: Account Access**

- **Name:** Create Account / Log In

- **Purpose:** Entry screen after downloading the app.

- **Details:**

  - Options to _Log In_ or _Create Account_ (email or social login).

  - Requires accepting **Terms** and **Privacy Policy**.

  - Prompts user to enter Venmo/Square/PayPal handle.

### **Screen 1: Wall of Flame (Homepage)**

- **Purpose:** Central gameplay hub displaying Hot Takes for rating.

- **Feed Rules:**

  - Shows Hot Takes sorted by _fewest ratings first_.

  - Every **4th Hot Take** alternates between a ‚Äútop rated‚Äù Take (highest average) and a ‚Äúmost voted‚Äù Take.

  - Every **7th Hot Take** slot is an **ad container**.

- **User Actions:**

  - Swipe or scroll vertically through Takes.

  - Drag rating slider (0‚Äì100 Scoville).

  - Press ‚ÄúSubmit‚Äù to lock in rating and see the current average.

### **Screen 2: Hall of Flame**

- **Purpose:** Weekly leaderboard archive.

- **Content:** Top 3 Hot Takes from the previous week in descending order (1st, 2nd, 3rd).

- **Features:**

  - Display user handle (anonymous alias).

  - Show each Take‚Äôs final Heat Score.

  - Visual trophy or flame icons to denote placement.

### **Screen 3: Take Creation Page**

- **Purpose:** Compose and submit a new Hot Take.

- **Features:**

  - Text field (30‚Äì150 characters).

  - Keyboard pop-up for input.

  - ‚ÄúSubmit Your Take‚Äù CTA button.

  - Character counter \+ disclaimer (‚ÄúNo hate speech or illegal content‚Äù).

### **Screen 4: Rewards Page**

- **Purpose:** Incentivize engagement and viral growth.

- **Details:**

  - Displays current **jackpot amount** and **active player count**.

  - Shows threshold for next prize tier.

  - ‚ÄúInvite your friends‚Äù button generates a personalized invite link (bit.ly shortlink) leading to iOS/Android store.

### **Screen 5: Profile Page**

- **Purpose:** Account and customization hub.

- **Features:**

  - Edit email and display name.

  - Select from pre-made **jalape√±o pepper icons** as avatars.

  - Update payment handle.

  - Access **Password Reset**, **Terms**, and **Privacy** links.

  - Links redirect to hosted webpages.

## **Content Sorting Algorithm**

To balance exposure and engagement:

1. **Equitable Distribution:**

   - Hot Takes are sorted by the **least number of ratings** (ascending).

   - Ensures newly submitted or unseen Takes receive visibility.

2. **Engagement Inserts:**

   - Every **4th Take** alternates between:

     - _Highest average-rated Take_ (quality highlight).

     - _Most voted Take_ (popularity highlight).

3. **Ad Monetization:**

   - Every **7th Take** position is an **ad slot** populated via an **ad server API**.

   - Ensures balanced content-to-ad ratio (\~17% ad density).

4. **Feed Refresh Logic:**

   - Players see a dynamic mix of low-rated and trending Takes upon every session refresh.

   - Prevents repetitive exposure and promotes discovery.

## **Engineering Architecture Considerations**

### **Backend Services**

- **Database:**

  - User database (account details, linked payment handles).

  - Content database (Hot Takes text, scores, timestamps).

  - Icon library database (for jalape√±o avatars).

  - Leaderboard table (weekly aggregates \+ winners).

- **Ad Infrastructure:**

  - Ad container placeholders dynamically inserted via algorithm.

  - Ad API integration with configurable refresh rates and targeting options.

- **Game Logic / Sorting:**

  - Sorting algorithm for equitable exposure (least-rated first).

  - Configurable weights to allow tuning between fairness and engagement.

  - Weekly cron job to archive results and reset the game cycle.

### **Analytics & Metrics**

- **Track:**

  - Total downloads (via bit.ly or Firebase dynamic links).

  - Weekly active users (WAU).

  - Number of Hot Takes submitted.

  - Total votes cast.

  - Ad impressions & CTR.

  - Invite link clicks (for virality tracking).

### **Platform**

- **Frontend:** React Native (cross-platform for iOS & Android).

- **Backend:** Node.js or Python (Flask/FastAPI) hosted on Firebase.

- **Storage:** Firestore for structured data; maybe S3 for assets or keep within Firebase.

- **Payments:** 3rd-party payout processing via Venmo, Square, or PayPal API (may not be required so long as we have a means of storing the handle somewhere we can payout manually at the start).

- **Scalability:** Microservice design to independently scale content delivery, analytics, and ad services.

## **Rewards**

The weekly jackpot scales dynamically with total **active players (AP)**‚Äîdefined as users who submit at least one Hot Take that week.

| Active Players (AP) | Prize Amount |
| ------------------- | ------------ |
| 1 ‚Äì 250             | $20          |
| 251 ‚Äì 750           | $30          |
| 751 ‚Äì 1,250         | $40          |
| 1,251 ‚Äì 2,000       | $60          |
| 2,001 ‚Äì 4,000       | $80          |
| 4,001+              | $100         |

### **Reward Design Considerations**

- **Virality:** The ‚ÄúInvite Your Friends‚Äù feature should highlight how close the community is to unlocking the next payout tier (e.g., ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre 210 players away from a $60 jackpot\!‚Äù).

- **Stickiness:** Showing progress toward higher prize tiers motivates sharing and sustained weekly participation.

- **Transparency:** A countdown clock and visible pot size on the Rewards page encourage daily check-ins.

- **Retention Mechanic:** Players notified mid-week of current leaderboard status via push notifications (‚ÄúYour Take is heating up\! You‚Äôre in the Top 10\!‚Äù).

## **Features (future)**

These are some eligible future-looking feature ideas that may enrich the app experience:

1. **Push Notifications:** Not that this needs to be too heavy handed, however ‚ÄúYour Take is heating up\! You‚Äôre in the Top 10\!‚Äù is a good one to let players know to remain invested. If the number of players needed to reach the next tier comes within 90% completion of that tier evolution, all players could get a ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre _n_ number of players away from a _$yy_ jackpot\! Invite your friends to play‚Äù

2. **Share:** we‚Äôll need a way for players to post their own or anonymous Hot Takes to social platforms or text group chats to help with virality. This will need a baked-in way to tag our Hot Takes owned social media pages so we can repost to boost visibility.

3. **My Takes:** This PRD does _not_ currently outline a way for players to see their own past **Takes**. This probably works best on the **Profiles** page, but will require more work and for an MVP I kind of like the fact that Takes just go out into the Ether and people only find out if they win at the end of the week. But this can be reconsidered as traffic ticks up or if players are like ‚Äúwhere the hell are all my **Takes**?\!‚Äù
